We are seeking proposals to implement margin trading functionality integrated with DeepBook V3. The solution must allow users to enter leveraged positions by borrowing funds, manage their collateral, and undergo automated liquidations when their collateral ratio falls below a set threshold. An external price oracle (e.g., Pyth) will act as the source of truth for asset pricing and collateral health monitoring.

## Desirable Features

* Borrowing and Lending: Enable users to borrow assets to increase their market exposure.  
* Collateral Management: Users must be able to deposit, manage, and monitor collateral associated with their leveraged positions.  
* Health Factor Monitoring: Real-time monitoring of position health based on price oracle feeds.  
* Liquidation Mechanism: Automated liquidation of under-collateralized positions, ensuring system solvency and user risk mitigation.  
* Oracle Integration: Integration with external decentralized oracles (e.g., Pyth Network) for reliable and tamper-proof price data.  
* Modular Design for Auditability: The system must be modular, with clearly separated components (e.g., borrowing logic, collateral management, liquidation, oracle integration) to enable easy auditing and security reviews. Each module must have clearly defined interfaces and limited interdependencies to reduce attack surface and facilitate third-party audits.
